Phyllonorycter ulicicolella is a moth of the family Gracillariidae. It is known from Great Britain, Spain, France, Italy and Greece.
The wingspan is 6â€“8 mm. The forewings are shining golden ochreous; a white median streak from base to near middle ;four short costal and three dorsal shining white wedge-shaped
spots, first dorsal long, second broad ; a black apical strigula; a black line in cilia.Hindwings are grey.Adults are on wing from June to August.The larvae feed on Ulex species. They mine the spines, shoots or bark of their host plant.